{
  "stem": "19807.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They formed some organizations which were called [NON-ENGLISH] and [NON-ENGLISH] like legions, and the [NON-ENGLISH], which are the defense.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They wore uniforms.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "They were like real fascists.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Then they began, if we were wandering in the main street, they would beat up on us or they would call us dirty names.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And it was the-- The first foremost sign to me was, I had joined the Boy Scouts, Bulgarian Boy Scouts.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And we would be going on-- on one of those hills.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And we would excel, we'd be studying the Morse code, with-- with flags.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "It was fascinating.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the friend that took me there, a Bulgarian friend from the neighborhood, one day very quietly comes to me, says to me, you can't come and be part of us anymore.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I said, why not?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I paid my dues.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He says, you're Jewish.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Jews are not allowed anymore to join the scouts.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "However, you have Hashomer Hatzair, which we had three factions in-- in-- in Plovdiv-- the Maccabees, the Hashomer Hatzair, and Betar.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "However, Hashomer Hatzair is like boy scouts.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I suggest that you go to them.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Well, I didn't.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I was belonging to the Maccabees anyway.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But it really hurt me to the point I went home crying.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And my mother had to comfort me and said, brace yourself.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Tough times are coming.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I couldn't understand that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So all of a sudden, you begin to see all these signs.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I told you that was the next sign, was when we were in temple, and the Bedouins began to come.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Now my father worked in a company which, the name of the company was [NON-ENGLISH] which means the-- the brothers Benjamin Levy.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "One of the brothers had just come back from Germany.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
